{
  "stem": "7832.4",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "So they said, for every person that's going to take their lives, they're going to torture to dead five of us.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "So, of course, everybody ignored the-- the barbed wire from then on in.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Nobody died at the wire from that-- from that day on.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "But there were other ways.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "It was-- the bathroom, we had one bathroom for 32,000 people.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "[?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "Teilager ?] had 32 barracks that people lived in.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "They had more barracks that they used for storage and the kitchen and whatever.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "But 32,000 people went to one latrine, once a day.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "So you can imagine the torture and the agony to-- until you were able to go.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And then the food you were given was meant to destroy us, not-- not to keep us alive.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "There was enough rations to keep us alive maybe for three months from the time of arrival until the time of death.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "Of course, thank God, a lot of us surprised them.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And-- and so the-- the-- the torture of being alive was always there, every second, every minute, everywhere.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "But now, we were the two of us left and, we weren't even allowed to be showing each other support, for fear that somebody will notice it and then we'll be separated again.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "But we were separated anyway.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "She was taken away.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "There were selections every single day, and the people were selected to be taken for certain-- for certain things.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "See, we weren't tattooed-- I wasn't tattooed right away.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "I was tattooed after they selected me for something, because then we found out that when we came in, that they were-- the reason we weren't tattooed right away is they didn't want us to live.",
      "word_count": 36
    }
  ],
